Project Context:

This is a school project: an online food ordering demo. The project uses:
- Python with Flask for backend
- MySQL for database (two tables: customers and orders)
- HTML/CSS (templates) for GUI
- JavaScript for interactive features (Add-to-Cart with toast notifications)

Current Setup:

1. Database:
   - Table `customers`: customer_id (AUTO_INCREMENT), name, gmail
   - Table `orders`: order_id (AUTO_INCREMENT), customer_id (FK), ordered_items, total_bill, date
2. Flask app (`app.py`) handles:
   - Home page (`index.html`) showing 4 food items with Add-to-Cart buttons
   - Cart page (`cart.html`) showing cart items and total bill
   - Order confirmation page (`success.html`) with green tick image, ordered items, total bill, date
   - Cart stored in Flask session
   - Add-to-Cart uses JS with toast notifications (non-blocking)
   - Go to Cart button on index page for navigating to cart
3. Frontend:
   - Templates in `templates/` folder: index.html, cart.html, success.html
   - Simple, clean GUI (no hover effects)
   - Toast notifications for Add-to-Cart instead of alerts
   - Green tick image on success page
4. Integration:
   - Fully compatible with Flask routing
   - Database interactions work via mysql-connector-python
   - No Jinja loops in HTML; uses separate variables for cart items (cart1, cart2, etc.)

